sitting all alone, drinking.

666
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:43,520
He came up to me and he said,

667
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:47,800
"I have always found your affair with
Clifford to be common and immoral."

668
00:41:47,920 --> 00:41:49,360
And he stormed out.

669
00:41:50,720 --> 00:41:52,920
You're lying. Elmyr didn't say that.

670
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:55,000
Oh, I'm the liar?

671
00:41:55,120 --> 00:41:59,000
And who's writing a fake book about
the most famous man in the world?

672
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:03,080
Gotta get back.

673
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:06,680
No! No, the clock is broken. You stay.

674
00:42:09,160 --> 00:42:10,760
Just to confirm,

675
00:42:11,200 --> 00:42:14,000
he's still rich
and you're still not gonna leave him.

676
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:16,680
Oh, I want to, Cliff, I want to.

677
00:42:17,200 --> 00:42:20,200
But, no, I'm not going to.

678
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:26,360
I'm shallow, Cliff.

679
00:42:28,160 --> 00:42:31,440
My greatest desire
is to be an American movie star.

680
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:34,200
- How shallow is that?
- Pretty shallow.

681
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:38,600
And besides, why does it bother you
so much that I'm your mistress?

682
00:42:38,720 --> 00:42:41,160
Brecht, Hemingway,
they all had mistresses.

683
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:44,800
The lying gives me a headache,
if you want to know the truth.

684
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:47,240
Oh, I forgot. You're a devoted husband.

685
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:50,240
I think I forgot
while you were screwing me.

686
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:54,840
Sorry.

687
00:42:56,560 --> 00:42:59,000
Sorry.
I know I should have not called you.

688
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:01,720
I'm not gonna go through
this whole thing again.

689
00:43:02,720 --> 00:43:05,600
I can't do it to her. I can't.

690
00:43:07,360 --> 00:43:08,920
I'll see you next time?

691
00:43:14,280 --> 00:43:17,040
Oh, Dick, Nina!
There's no future with her.

692
00:43:17,520 --> 00:43:20,040
- She weakens me.
- Okay, all right. That's very helpful.

693
00:43:20,160 --> 00:43:22,520
Edith is stability, Dick. She's my rock.

694
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:24,640
Give me a break, will you, please?

695
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:27,080
Did you tell Nina about the book?

696
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:30,080
Are you out of your fucking mind?

697
00:43:30,200 --> 00:43:32,760
I've got the "I'm an asshole" part
down pretty good.

698
00:43:32,880 --> 00:43:35,080
It's the "What do I do now?" part
I need help with.

699
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:37,120
Please? Be my friend?

700
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,240
- Are you my friend?
- Yeah, I'm your friend.

701
00:43:39,360 --> 00:43:42,760
I don't know what I'm gonna do
if she asks me where I went.

702
00:43:43,200 --> 00:43:44,440
Come clean.

703
00:43:45,840 --> 00:43:47,760
She'll leave me, for good.

704
00:43:48,680 --> 00:43:51,160
It's the best I got.
What else can I tell you?

705
00:43:52,760 --> 00:43:54,160
You wanna hear this?

706
00:43:55,360 --> 00:43:56,360
Yeah.

707
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:58,840
All right,
this is the Senate hearings, 1947.

708
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:02,040
I'm not even sure
that's a correct statement,

709
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:06,520
but the fact remains
that if I made 15 million dollars,

710
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:10,000
I made it selling oil well tools
and beer,

711
00:44:10,080 --> 00:44:13,080
Grand Prize beer,
to people down in Texas.

712
00:44:13,160 --> 00:44:14,840
"Beer down in Texas."

713
00:44:16,160 --> 00:44:20,000
And I don't think the public
should be led to believe...

714
00:44:20,120 --> 00:44:21,760
"Led to believe."

715
00:44:21,880 --> 00:44:24,920
...on war contracts while I did not.
Now, furthermore...

716
00:44:25,000 --> 00:44:26,760
"Now, furthermore..."

717
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:29,080
- "Furthermore, Senator..."
- "Furthermore..."

718
00:44:29,160 --> 00:44:32,240
...a little money somewhere.
How could I put nine million dollars...

719
00:44:32,320 --> 00:44:33,800
A little pocket change

720
00:44:33,920 --> 00:44:36,920
worth five million dollars in my pocket.

721
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:41,160
Mr. Hughes, where would you
like to begin?

722
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:45,840
- Family, friends, father...
- Yeah.

723
00:44:45,960 --> 00:44:47,760
My father. We'll do father.

724
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:56,400
People called my father Big Howard.

725
00:44:58,160 --> 00:44:59,360
Big Howard...

726
00:45:00,200 --> 00:45:04,840
Big Howard made his money
leasing drilling bits in the oil business.

727
00:45:07,200 --> 00:45:09,400
He said to me... He said, "Sonny..."

728
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:14,920
"Sonny, these drill bits
are your bread and butter.

729
00:45:15,040 --> 00:45:16,760
"Don't ever let 'em go."

730
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:23,880
Big Howard died when I was 18.

731
00:45:26,720 --> 00:45:32,200
His bunch of Texas roughneck friends
tried to sell his company.

732
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:37,440
Pushed me out of the picture.
I don't like being pushed.

733
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:44,920
Now, when two parties negotiate,
you got a lion and a donkey.

734
00:45:48,400 --> 00:45:51,960
One party, through bluster or leverage,

735
00:45:53,400 --> 00:45:56,720
claims control of
the situation right away. That's the lion.

736
00:45:58,800 --> 00:46:00,120
At 18,

737
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:03,320
I sued these men
trying to sell my father's company.

738
00:46:03,440 --> 00:46:05,840
I sued them, I attacked them,
I blackmailed them,

739
00:46:05,960 --> 00:46:09,440
I pushed every which way I could!

740
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:13,240
I learned to be a lion.

741
00:46:27,280 --> 00:46:28,640
Jesus, Cliff.

742
00:46:37,760 --> 00:46:40,080
- Read the women's rags lately?
- Hi.

743
00:46:40,800 --> 00:46:43,600
Excerpts from
Howard Hughes' autobiography

744
00:46:43,680 --> 00:46:47,240
in Ladies Home Journal
from the book by Robert Eaton.

745
00:46:49,440 --> 00:46:51,960
Life's lawyers are gnawing
the flesh from my bones.

746
00:46:52,080 --> 00:46:55,079
Would you like to tell me, Clifford,
what the fuck is going on here?

747
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:56,280
I don't know anything about this.

748
00:46:56,400 --> 00:46:58,320
This goddamn Eaton
supposedly has memos,

749
00:46:58,440 --> 00:47:01,480
the same handwritten memos
that you've got, so...

750
00:47:01,920 --> 00:47:04,760
Either you're selling this twice and
using Robert Eaton as a pen name...

751
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:06,880
I won't even dignify that
with a response.

752
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:12,240
Or, more likely, your demigod
lunatic friend is using two writers.

753
00:47:12,360 --> 00:47:13,360
You get it?

754
00:47:13,480 --> 00:47:15,440
All the sharks at my company
have is you,

755
00:47:15,560 --> 00:47:20,120
which means they will sue your skinny
ass for every cent of the advance,

756
00:47:20,200 --> 00:47:22,760
plus damages,
for making false representations...

757
00:47:22,880 --> 00:47:24,080
No, I made no false representations!

758
00:47:24,160 --> 00:47:27,040
...about an exclusive book
you said you could deliver.

759
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:29,720
So she said that they said
that they would sue us both?

760
00:47:29,800 --> 00:47:30,800
- Yeah.
- Both of us?

761
00:47:30,880 --> 00:47:32,880
- I mean, she mentioned me by name?
- Yes.

762
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:35,080
Can you believe this son of a bitch
had the same idea?

763
00:47:35,200 --> 00:47:36,920
But I spent the money.

764
00:47:37,440 --> 00:47:40,320
I told you we might have to give it back!
Jeez, Dick.

765
00:47:40,440 --> 00:47:42,680
Well, it wasn't exactly
a huge percentage to begin with.

766
00:47:42,760 --> 00:47:43,920
Look, just pay the money.

767
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:46,880
Tell them that Hughes
has changed his mind.

768
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:50,560
- And I'll owe you the difference.
- I can't. I'm down most of it myself.

769
00:47:50,680 --> 00:47:53,920
Yeah, well, borrow it.
This isn't a prank anymore, Cliff.

770
00:47:54,040 --> 00:47:55,800
If they go to the press with this,

771
00:47:55,920 --> 00:47:58,160
we're gonna have
Howard fucking Hughes chasing us.

772
00:47:58,240 --> 00:47:59,400
And Intertel.

773
00:47:59,520 --> 00:48:02,200
Remember, they'll stab us
with sodium pentothal?

774
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:05,840
They'll kill us or tie us up or something.

775
00:48:06,160 --> 00:48:10,000
Howard won't be coming after us.
His advisors maybe, but he won't.

776
00:48:10,120 --> 00:48:11,120
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

777
00:48:11,240 --> 00:48:12,720
- What, he tell you that over breakfast?
- Yeah.

778
00:48:12,800 --> 00:48:14,840
And what about this other book?
What if that's the real thing, huh?

779
00:48:14,960 --> 00:48:16,480
You thought about that?

780
00:48:16,920 --> 00:48:18,000
All right, the question is,

781
00:48:18,080 --> 00:48:20,120
what would Howard do
in a situation like this?

782
00:48:20,240 --> 00:48:22,320
I don't know. Buy a fucking airline.

783
00:48:24,280 --> 00:48:27,720
Diversion, end run, surprise.

784
00:48:29,800 --> 00:48:31,720
Who are you now? General Patton?

785
00:48:32,160 --> 00:48:35,600
Viruses and bacteria
are the most powerful enemies...

786
00:48:40,080 --> 00:48:41,240
Luce.

787
00:48:42,560 --> 00:48:45,200
...the human body has got.
You look at the fingernail clippings...

788
00:48:45,280 --> 00:48:46,960
Henry Luce.

789
00:48:50,160 --> 00:48:52,680
Dick, I think you should
take a little holiday.

790
00:48:53,160 --> 00:48:54,640
You got everything?
You got your passport?

791
00:48:54,760 --> 00:48:56,120
- You got the letter? Okay, great.
- Yeah, I'm fine...

792
00:48:56,200 --> 00:48:57,680
You're gonna be fine. Bye.

793
00:49:30,600 --> 00:49:32,560
- Hello, this is Andrea.
- Yeah, Andrea, it's Cliff.

794
00:49:32,680 --> 00:49:34,840
Yeah, one more thing, Shelton Fisher
needs to be at the meeting.

795
00:49:34,920 --> 00:49:36,120
Do you know who he is?

796
00:49:36,200 --> 00:49:37,800
Chairman of McGraw-Hill, yes.

797
00:49:37,920 --> 00:49:40,080
- Has to be at the meeting.
- All right, I'll see what I can do.

798
00:49:40,160 --> 00:49:43,960
It's not me. It's him.
No negotiation. No Fisher, no meeting.

799
00:49:54,560 --> 00:49:58,480
Mr. Irving, it would appear
that either you

800
00:49:58,560 --> 00:50:02,200
or your illustrious sponsor
is jerking someone's chain.

801
00:50:02,640 --> 00:50:06,200
Let me assure you that chain
will not be connected to Life magazine.

802
00:50:07,320 --> 00:50:11,560
So, why don't you begin by telling us
who Robert Eaton is

803
00:50:11,680 --> 00:50:15,080
and why he's selling the book
you're supposed to be writing?

804
00:50:17,480 --> 00:50:19,840
Shelton, have you received
your mail today?

805
00:50:22,120 --> 00:50:23,360
Excuse me?

806
00:50:24,120 --> 00:50:26,000
Ralph, I was talking to Shelton.

807
00:50:26,320 --> 00:50:28,600
As a side comment,
watch your tone with me.

808
00:50:28,720 --> 00:50:32,040
I've been up for two nights negotiating
with a very stubborn billionaire,

809
00:50:32,160 --> 00:50:34,680
and my quota for verbal abuse
has been reached.

810
00:50:38,240 --> 00:50:40,120
Could you get the mail, please?

811
00:50:40,800 --> 00:50:43,040
Life magazine has been known

812
00:50:43,160 --> 00:50:46,360
to have a slight impact
on writers' careers, my friend.

813
00:50:46,440 --> 00:50:50,040
And we...
We are not afraid of civil litigation.

